nodes.text: 26-424 was an individual from Galloway Island. 26-424 belonged to a species that possessed dark eyes, a tail, two legs, at least one arm, and a horn on the head. 26-424, as usual, refused to participate in a periodical seminar that, at least on one occasion, featured eminent figures such as Regalia Sub-space station-12 director mOKDAR 15, Manifold Mollusk Matrix and Matrimony Association director Skreen, and University of Desultori scholar and author Aanxi Raanxi Laanxi, although 26-424 had presence confirmed for the feedings.

26-424 was introduced in a segment named "The Seminar Participants," written by Bob Carrau for the 1993 book Monsters and Aliens from George Lucas, a publication that collects concept designs and photographs from various George Lucas projects. Lucasfilm employee Leland Chee, who maintains the Holocron continuity database, has indicated that information contained in the book is non-canonical.
